1
00:00:15,808 --> 00:00:19,136
(Luolianke City Hall Office)

2
00:00:25,721 --> 00:00:27,681
Tu Jiasheng.

3
00:00:27,681 --> 00:00:29,280
Tu Jiasheng.

4
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:31,760
He is certainly capable.

5
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:34,600
But right now, these three brothers

6
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:38,001
seem a bit off.

7
00:00:42,964 --> 00:00:43,763
I'm listening.

8
00:00:46,163 --> 00:00:48,524
Pick me up an hour early
for tomorrow's meeting.

9
00:00:50,403 --> 00:00:52,324
This is my first work report

10
00:00:52,483 --> 00:00:54,964
since taking office as mayor.

11
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,284
Arriving early is essential.

12
00:00:57,443 --> 00:00:58,324
That's it.

13
00:01:10,004 --> 00:01:10,963
What now?

14
00:01:11,443 --> 00:01:12,243
Deputy Mayor He,

15
00:01:13,163 --> 00:01:14,323
I'm Zhao.

16
00:01:17,044 --> 00:01:18,044
Mr. Zhao,

17
00:01:18,443 --> 00:01:20,083
calling at this hour,

18
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:20,992
are you telling me

19
00:01:20,992 --> 00:01:23,044
good news from Mr. Tu?

20
00:01:23,204 --> 00:01:24,684
I'm afraid I have bad news.

21
00:01:29,883 --> 00:01:31,243
What bad news?

22
00:01:31,963 --> 00:01:33,443
Cong, your son,

23
00:01:34,124 --> 00:01:35,284
had quite a bit to drink

24
00:01:35,523 --> 00:01:36,603
and left our place.

25
00:01:37,883 --> 00:01:38,844
He's gone

26
00:01:39,883 --> 00:01:41,124
in a car accident.

27
00:01:42,163 --> 00:01:43,564
Please accept my condolences.

28
00:02:03,808 --> 00:02:06,880
=The Glory Fades=

29
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:09,728
=Episode 7=
(Back in the Lion's Den)

30
00:02:25,043 --> 00:02:25,684
Sir,

31
00:02:25,684 --> 00:02:28,124
crystal meth was found
in the ashes at the scene.

32
00:02:29,043 --> 00:02:29,923
Before the accident,

33
00:02:29,923 --> 00:02:31,520
Cong was likely using it.

34
00:02:31,923 --> 00:02:32,603
Idiots!

35
00:02:35,844 --> 00:02:37,043
Pass this down.

36
00:02:38,163 --> 00:02:40,284
Make sure everyone
keeps their mouths shut.

37
00:02:41,323 --> 00:02:42,564
Lock down the scene thoroughly.

38
00:02:43,084 --> 00:02:44,964
Not a single mosquito gets through.

39
00:02:45,728 --> 00:02:46,404
Understood.

40
00:02:47,244 --> 00:02:48,564
As to those surveillance feeds,

41
00:02:49,364 --> 00:02:50,483
including He Cong's

42
00:02:51,524 --> 00:02:54,524
route surveillance from tonight.

43
00:02:54,524 --> 00:02:55,923
Compile it all for me.

44
00:02:56,163 --> 00:02:57,643
There can only be one copy.

45
00:02:58,043 --> 00:02:59,804
No backups allowed for anyone.

46
00:03:00,244 --> 00:03:00,804
Understood.

47
00:03:08,124 --> 00:03:09,084
Go handle

48
00:03:09,643 --> 00:03:10,804
that woman

49
00:03:10,912 --> 00:03:12,043
and the driver's family.

50
00:03:12,256 --> 00:03:13,763
Make sure they learn to stay silent.

51
00:03:14,723 --> 00:03:15,684
Don't worry, sir.

52
00:03:16,804 --> 00:03:17,643
Go now.

53
00:03:18,043 --> 00:03:18,844
I'm fine.

54
00:03:19,723 --> 00:03:20,524
Yes.

55
00:03:27,564 --> 00:03:28,163
Hello,

56
00:03:28,323 --> 00:03:29,203
Deputy Mayor He.

57
00:03:29,804 --> 00:03:31,284
I heard about Cong.

58
00:03:31,844 --> 00:03:34,564
You bear such a heavy burden,
serving the country and the people.

59
00:03:34,564 --> 00:03:35,483
It's very demanding.

60
00:03:35,964 --> 00:03:38,244
Recently, you held
such an important work report meeting.

61
00:03:38,763 --> 00:03:39,552
Please take care

62
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:40,524
of your health.

63
00:03:41,723 --> 00:03:43,163
Right now, I just want to know

64
00:03:43,404 --> 00:03:44,564
who exactly

65
00:03:44,844 --> 00:03:46,244
killed my son.

66
00:03:46,804 --> 00:03:47,564
Killed?

67
00:03:48,923 --> 00:03:50,043
You mean

68
00:03:50,404 --> 00:03:52,524
someone deliberately caused
this accident?

69
00:03:56,124 --> 00:03:57,004
Mr. He,

70
00:03:57,483 --> 00:03:58,763
you're overthinking it.

71
00:03:59,244 --> 00:04:00,323
But for now,

72
00:04:00,723 --> 00:04:01,684
let me just say,

73
00:04:02,124 --> 00:04:03,163
accept my condolences.

74
00:04:03,723 --> 00:04:04,923
Yes.

75
00:04:05,284 --> 00:04:06,404
There's no other way.

76
00:04:08,043 --> 00:04:09,284
It's fate.

77
00:04:09,763 --> 00:04:11,883
You can't fight fate.

78
00:04:12,364 --> 00:04:13,244
That's right.

79
00:04:13,888 --> 00:04:14,883
I'll leave it at that.

80
00:04:15,744 --> 00:04:16,643
Goodbye.

81
00:04:20,084 --> 00:04:21,483
Much powder was found at the scene.

82
00:04:22,403 --> 00:04:23,203
No survivors.

83
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:24,883
It's clear as day.

84
00:04:28,443 --> 00:04:30,323
Mr. He has sealed the news.

85
00:04:30,523 --> 00:04:31,883
Saves face, I suppose.

86
00:04:34,604 --> 00:04:35,364
Why?

87
00:04:38,164 --> 00:04:38,843
Cong and his dad

88
00:04:38,843 --> 00:04:39,763
are still useful to us.

89
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,763
And currently, they pose no threat.

90
00:04:43,168 --> 00:04:44,164
Why didn't you tell me?

91
00:04:48,164 --> 00:04:49,643
He wanted to investigate Manni.

92
00:04:49,883 --> 00:04:51,963
I was worried if he found something,
and harmed...

93
00:04:51,963 --> 00:04:53,083
Are you worried about Manni

94
00:04:53,216 --> 00:04:54,484
or about Deep In The Bustle?

95
00:04:54,523 --> 00:04:55,323
Or rather

96
00:04:55,443 --> 00:04:56,843
was this Feng's idea?

97
00:04:57,004 --> 00:04:58,403
He has nothing to do with this.

98
00:05:01,216 --> 00:05:02,323
This was my mistake.

99
00:05:03,484 --> 00:05:04,883
Should have discussed it with you.

100
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:07,403
I'll take my punishment.

101
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:26,044
Tonight,

102
00:05:26,044 --> 00:05:27,244
are you meeting

103
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:28,044
Tang Niansong?

104
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:28,484
Yes.

105
00:05:28,604 --> 00:05:29,364
At 6:00 PM

106
00:05:29,364 --> 00:05:30,124
in Room 333.

107
00:05:31,203 --> 00:05:32,576
Room 333?

108
00:05:33,124 --> 00:05:34,283
You should freshen up.

109
00:05:34,283 --> 00:05:34,883
Take a shower.

110
00:05:34,883 --> 00:05:35,763
You're tired.

111
00:05:35,963 --> 00:05:37,523
After all, he's a governor.

112
00:05:37,604 --> 00:05:38,496
Show him some respect.

113
00:05:39,643 --> 00:05:41,643
Even a deputy governor deserves
our respect.

114
00:05:41,724 --> 00:05:42,336
The three of us

115
00:05:42,336 --> 00:05:43,604
have fallen to this point.

116
00:05:43,643 --> 00:05:45,004
Have you ever heard this saying?

117
00:05:45,843 --> 00:05:46,523
A mighty dragon

118
00:05:46,604 --> 00:05:47,843
doesn't swim with mudfish.

119
00:05:47,883 --> 00:05:48,403
A phoenix

120
00:05:48,403 --> 00:05:49,523
doesn't flock with sparrows.

121
00:05:50,203 --> 00:05:51,712
Where would I have heard that?

122
00:05:51,712 --> 00:05:52,924
I studied in the U.S.,

123
00:05:52,924 --> 00:05:53,604
Jiasheng.

124
00:05:56,804 --> 00:05:57,804
Mr. Tang

125
00:05:57,804 --> 00:05:58,684
is a scholar.

126
00:05:58,804 --> 00:06:00,804
Worked at the Education Bureau
for ten years,

127
00:06:00,883 --> 00:06:02,963
and jumped three levels
to become deputy governor.

128
00:06:03,004 --> 00:06:03,763
Think about it.

129
00:06:05,056 --> 00:06:06,684
I actually have heard of him.

130
00:06:07,244 --> 00:06:08,924
Tough to deal with,
he has his connections.

131
00:06:16,128 --> 00:06:17,604
Don't tell Feng

132
00:06:18,124 --> 00:06:19,443
I'm meeting Tang Niansong.

133
00:06:20,403 --> 00:06:21,244
After all,

134
00:06:21,484 --> 00:06:22,164
if it goes wrong,

135
00:06:22,164 --> 00:06:22,963
he would...

136
00:06:22,963 --> 00:06:23,443
You know.

137
00:06:23,523 --> 00:06:24,323
I understand.

138
00:06:25,283 --> 00:06:26,283
Go get some sleep.

139
00:06:26,283 --> 00:06:27,283
Haven't slept all night.

140
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:29,883
Alright.

141
00:06:30,244 --> 00:06:30,724
Go on.

142
00:06:32,643 --> 00:06:33,804
Are you a penguin?

143
00:06:33,804 --> 00:06:34,924
The room's so cold.

144
00:06:38,443 --> 00:06:39,604
If Ruoxi were here,

145
00:06:39,883 --> 00:06:41,083
she would have reminded you.

146
00:06:42,684 --> 00:06:43,244
I'm leaving.

147
00:06:55,443 --> 00:06:56,484
26 Celsius Degrees,

148
00:06:56,684 --> 00:06:57,883
a comfortable temperature.

149
00:06:59,004 --> 00:07:00,203
26?

150
00:07:00,684 --> 00:07:01,724
That is too high.

151
00:07:02,244 --> 00:07:03,083
20.

152
00:07:03,643 --> 00:07:04,443
24.

153
00:07:04,684 --> 00:07:05,724
No lower.

154
00:07:08,484 --> 00:07:09,643
22?

155
00:07:10,724 --> 00:07:11,684
Fine.

156
00:07:12,083 --> 00:07:13,472
22 it is.

157
00:07:14,523 --> 00:07:15,523
Listen,

158
00:07:15,883 --> 00:07:17,124
you're still drunk,

159
00:07:17,124 --> 00:07:18,403
so you feel hot.

160
00:07:18,924 --> 00:07:20,083
When you wake up...

161
00:07:32,883 --> 00:07:33,963
Let me go!

162
00:07:35,244 --> 00:07:36,443
I'll count to three.

163
00:07:36,643 --> 00:07:37,763
Let go of me!

164
00:07:37,763 --> 00:07:41,098
♪Back to the day we first met♪

165
00:07:41,364 --> 00:07:42,164
Why?

166
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,283
Why do you always try to run?

167
00:07:46,684 --> 00:07:48,203
Your embrace is a gentle refuge,

168
00:07:49,604 --> 00:07:50,724
but it harbors poison.

169
00:07:52,576 --> 00:07:55,684
♪Back to the day we first met♪

170
00:07:55,684 --> 00:07:56,224
Poison?

171
00:07:56,224 --> 00:08:02,005
♪Let me love you all over again♪

172
00:08:03,684 --> 00:08:04,643
Jiasheng,

173
00:08:06,124 --> 00:08:07,083
why me?

174
00:08:07,264 --> 00:08:10,634
♪Light a cigarette,
watch it die and glow again♪

175
00:08:10,944 --> 00:08:12,992
♪My eyes are filled with the past♪

176
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:17,888
♪But I can't wait for you to look back♪

177
00:08:17,888 --> 00:08:21,184
♪I won't go, my dear♪

178
00:08:21,184 --> 00:08:26,837
♪Close your eyes and count to three♪

179
00:08:30,323 --> 00:08:31,364
Hello, Manni.

180
00:08:31,443 --> 00:08:31,963
Mr. Tu,

181
00:08:32,484 --> 00:08:33,664
all of Tang Niansong's info

182
00:08:33,664 --> 00:08:34,643
are ready.

183
00:08:34,724 --> 00:08:36,044
Should I bring them up now?

184
00:08:37,044 --> 00:08:37,684
Come up.

185
00:08:59,163 --> 00:09:00,004
(Tang Niansong)
Mr. Tang.

186
00:09:00,004 --> 00:09:00,896
(Deputy Governor of Danding State)

187
00:09:01,923 --> 00:09:02,604
Mr. Zhao.

188
00:09:03,244 --> 00:09:03,803
No.

189
00:09:03,844 --> 00:09:04,964
Here,

190
00:09:04,964 --> 00:09:06,084
they call you Lu.

191
00:09:06,244 --> 00:09:07,324
Hello, Lu.

192
00:09:07,324 --> 00:09:08,763
Greeted me personally at the door.

193
00:09:08,763 --> 00:09:09,643
Much appreciated.

194
00:09:10,084 --> 00:09:11,324
Not at all.

195
00:09:11,563 --> 00:09:12,244
I was worried

196
00:09:12,244 --> 00:09:13,803
that as a scholar,

197
00:09:14,004 --> 00:09:15,523
you'd look down on our establishment.

198
00:09:15,923 --> 00:09:16,964
Not true.

199
00:09:18,124 --> 00:09:18,763
Shall we

200
00:09:18,763 --> 00:09:19,604
talk inside?

201
00:09:19,683 --> 00:09:20,563
What about...

202
00:09:20,923 --> 00:09:21,643
Mr. Tu?

203
00:09:22,444 --> 00:09:23,523
He's on his way,

204
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:24,403
arriving shortly.

205
00:09:25,043 --> 00:09:26,244
Come in for some fine tea.

206
00:09:37,244 --> 00:09:38,084
Lu,

207
00:09:38,084 --> 00:09:40,364
I've heard that the third floor
of Deep In The Bustle

208
00:09:40,364 --> 00:09:41,248
is quite exclusive.

209
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:42,324
Eight VIP rooms in total,

210
00:09:42,324 --> 00:09:43,563
numbered from 111 to 999.

211
00:09:43,563 --> 00:09:44,763
Used according to rank.

212
00:09:56,084 --> 00:09:56,923
Mr. Tang,

213
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,324
small business.

214
00:09:58,324 --> 00:09:59,204
Better no rumors.

215
00:09:59,444 --> 00:10:00,563
Indeed eight rooms.

216
00:10:01,364 --> 00:10:03,004
Higher-ups have visited a few times.

217
00:10:03,444 --> 00:10:04,244
But

218
00:10:05,084 --> 00:10:05,883
it's all just gossip

219
00:10:05,883 --> 00:10:08,084
spread by those outside.

220
00:10:08,244 --> 00:10:09,444
Please just take it as a joke.

221
00:10:09,883 --> 00:10:10,643
Don't overthink it.

222
00:10:16,964 --> 00:10:18,244
The lobby isn't much to see.

223
00:10:18,403 --> 00:10:19,004
This way.

224
00:10:19,324 --> 00:10:20,204
After you.

225
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:46,400
(Lin Shen,
Son of the Energy Bureau Director)

226
00:10:50,043 --> 00:10:50,923
Miss,

227
00:10:51,043 --> 00:10:52,163
your hand

228
00:10:52,244 --> 00:10:52,923
is even smoother

229
00:10:52,923 --> 00:10:55,004
than my mother's family heirloom

230
00:10:55,683 --> 00:10:56,523
emerald bracelet.

231
00:10:59,124 --> 00:11:00,163
You flatter me.

232
00:11:00,288 --> 00:11:01,844
Your glass is empty.

233
00:11:01,844 --> 00:11:03,204
Let me refill it for you.

234
00:11:03,803 --> 00:11:04,683
A college student?

235
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,912
I could tell as soon as you spoke.

236
00:11:06,912 --> 00:11:07,403
Yes.

237
00:11:07,403 --> 00:11:08,324
I am currently...

238
00:11:09,683 --> 00:11:10,364
Resign.

239
00:11:10,592 --> 00:11:11,444
Leave this place.

240
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:12,803
For your own good.

241
00:11:13,403 --> 00:11:14,923
Mr. Tu feels you don't fit in here.

242
00:11:15,523 --> 00:11:16,324
You should leave.

243
00:11:16,724 --> 00:11:17,923
(Alright,)

244
00:11:17,923 --> 00:11:18,724
(I'll endure it.)

245
00:11:18,912 --> 00:11:20,283
(Unless I find the truth,)

246
00:11:20,563 --> 00:11:22,724
(no one can make me leave.)

247
00:11:40,364 --> 00:11:40,883
Sir,

248
00:11:41,124 --> 00:11:41,763
please drink.

249
00:11:42,563 --> 00:11:43,244
Can't get it.

250
00:11:46,523 --> 00:11:47,803
Still can't get it.

251
00:11:55,484 --> 00:11:56,883
What perfume are you wearing?

252
00:11:58,403 --> 00:11:59,724
It's so sweet it makes me dizzy.

253
00:11:59,724 --> 00:12:00,244
Come here.

254
00:12:02,163 --> 00:12:03,204
Feel my heart.

255
00:12:03,392 --> 00:12:04,403
Isn't it racing?

256
00:12:06,364 --> 00:12:07,563
Your heart is racing,

257
00:12:07,563 --> 00:12:08,364
Mr. Lin.

258
00:12:09,763 --> 00:12:10,484
Because you've

259
00:12:10,484 --> 00:12:12,244
drunk too much too quickly.

260
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:13,403
Here,

261
00:12:13,923 --> 00:12:15,523
let me add some ice for you

262
00:12:15,763 --> 00:12:16,683
to slow down a bit.

263
00:12:17,923 --> 00:12:18,403
Fine.

264
00:12:18,484 --> 00:12:19,163
You're

265
00:12:19,403 --> 00:12:20,244
very considerate.

266
00:12:20,763 --> 00:12:21,763
But the ice cubes

267
00:12:21,964 --> 00:12:22,763
aren't soothing.

268
00:12:22,964 --> 00:12:23,392
Come here.

269
00:12:23,683 --> 00:12:24,444
Let me hold you.

270
00:12:24,763 --> 00:12:25,844
A hug cures all ills.

271
00:12:26,844 --> 00:12:27,844
Mr. Lin,

272
00:12:28,124 --> 00:12:29,952
I'm no miracle cure.

273
00:12:30,364 --> 00:12:31,124
Besides,

274
00:12:31,444 --> 00:12:32,643
if I were that effective,

275
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,883
Mr. Tu

276
00:12:34,124 --> 00:12:36,124
would have promoted me
to the Tian Level long ago.

277
00:12:38,604 --> 00:12:39,403
Manni,

278
00:12:39,523 --> 00:12:40,563
copy?

279
00:12:42,084 --> 00:12:43,124
I'll sing a song with you.

280
00:12:43,484 --> 00:12:44,444
No.

281
00:12:45,244 --> 00:12:46,364
Just let me hold you.

282
00:12:47,124 --> 00:12:48,043
Sing one.

283
00:12:50,563 --> 00:12:51,523
What's going on?

284
00:12:51,683 --> 00:12:53,084
Is your equipment this bad?

285
00:12:53,283 --> 00:12:54,844
Mr. Lin.

286
00:12:59,604 --> 00:13:01,403
So sorry, Mr. Lin.

287
00:13:02,084 --> 00:13:02,844
Mr. Lin,

288
00:13:02,844 --> 00:13:04,004
let me toast you.

289
00:13:06,563 --> 00:13:07,563
Are you okay?

290
00:13:08,004 --> 00:13:08,683
I'm fine.

291
00:13:08,964 --> 00:13:10,124
You need to be careful too.

292
00:13:11,883 --> 00:13:12,844
You're a bit clumsy.

293
00:13:12,844 --> 00:13:13,604
Wait at the door.

294
00:13:14,124 --> 00:13:14,643
Yu,

295
00:13:15,043 --> 00:13:16,204
attend to Mr. Lin.

296
00:13:17,844 --> 00:13:18,844
She can't leave!

297
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:19,763
Mr. Lin,

298
00:13:20,163 --> 00:13:21,444
I just remembered,

299
00:13:21,763 --> 00:13:23,724
in three days, your father

300
00:13:23,724 --> 00:13:25,484
has a dinner appointment with Mr. Tu.

301
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:26,484
And

302
00:13:26,724 --> 00:13:27,763
I will definitely be there

303
00:13:27,844 --> 00:13:29,124
to properly toast him.

304
00:13:30,043 --> 00:13:31,364
Don't tell him that I'm here.

305
00:13:31,844 --> 00:13:33,084
He's a real hypocrite

306
00:13:33,084 --> 00:13:34,444
that only he can

307
00:13:34,444 --> 00:13:35,444
come to such a place.

308
00:13:37,484 --> 00:13:39,683
You do have a way with jokes.

309
00:13:39,763 --> 00:13:41,244
That's called love runs deep,

310
00:13:41,244 --> 00:13:42,523
and scolding shows care.

311
00:13:43,043 --> 00:13:43,563
Here.

312
00:13:45,444 --> 00:13:46,204
Mr. Lin,

313
00:13:46,403 --> 00:13:47,444
a toast to you.

314
00:13:58,923 --> 00:13:59,604
Manni,

315
00:13:59,803 --> 00:14:01,004
take her to the third floor.

316
00:14:01,004 --> 00:14:02,204
- Enjoy yourselves.
- Mr. Lin,

317
00:14:04,004 --> 00:14:05,364
to welcome your arrival,

318
00:14:05,664 --> 00:14:07,643
we present our signature drink,

319
00:14:09,324 --> 00:14:10,283
Volcanic Eruption

320
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:11,403
to you.

321
00:14:14,244 --> 00:14:15,324
Are you all insane?

322
00:14:15,324 --> 00:14:17,444
Have you lost your mind?

323
00:14:18,683 --> 00:14:20,084
Yunian, are you alright?

324
00:14:20,444 --> 00:14:21,043
I'm fine.

325
00:14:21,283 --> 00:14:21,964
Thank you,

326
00:14:21,964 --> 00:14:22,763
Ruxue.

327
00:14:23,244 --> 00:14:24,364
Oh, don't thank me.

328
00:14:24,563 --> 00:14:25,283
You should

329
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:26,484
thank Ms. Bai.

330
00:14:26,604 --> 00:14:27,204
She

331
00:14:27,204 --> 00:14:29,004
sent me personally to bail you out.

332
00:14:29,364 --> 00:14:30,964
Ms. Bai, thank you.

333
00:14:31,484 --> 00:14:32,283
No need for thanks.

334
00:14:32,563 --> 00:14:33,604
Mr. Tu's order.

335
00:14:33,923 --> 00:14:34,964
I'm just carrying it out.

336
00:14:35,883 --> 00:14:37,484
You really are blessed.

337
00:14:37,923 --> 00:14:38,848
As a newcomer,

338
00:14:38,848 --> 00:14:40,204
you've caught Mr. Tu's attention.

339
00:14:41,563 --> 00:14:42,324
Let's go.

340
00:14:44,923 --> 00:14:46,523
Oh, I've arranged in three days

341
00:14:46,563 --> 00:14:48,364
to meet two key Cabinet confidants.

342
00:14:48,576 --> 00:14:49,923
The Nordic route we discussed

343
00:14:49,923 --> 00:14:51,244
should be finalized this time.

344
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:52,204
Good.

345
00:14:52,736 --> 00:14:53,844
Ms. Bai,

346
00:14:53,844 --> 00:14:54,923
let me report to you.

347
00:14:55,084 --> 00:14:55,803
Tomorrow,

348
00:14:55,803 --> 00:14:58,204
I'm meeting Mr. Zhou
from the County Office.

349
00:14:58,403 --> 00:14:59,124
He has

350
00:14:59,124 --> 00:15:00,084
two spots available.

351
00:15:00,204 --> 00:15:01,563
I'll try to secure both in one go.

352
00:15:01,563 --> 00:15:02,883
Okay. Let's consolidate later.

353
00:15:03,084 --> 00:15:04,523
(According to Ruoxi's diary,)

354
00:15:04,523 --> 00:15:07,072
(here is the most mysterious
third floor of Deep In The Bustle.)

355
00:15:07,163 --> 00:15:09,763
(Tu Jiasheng's Room 999
should be just ahead.)

356
00:15:09,964 --> 00:15:11,484
Su Yunian?

357
00:15:11,563 --> 00:15:12,563
What are you doing here?

358
00:15:12,643 --> 00:15:14,523
You're supposed
to serve Mr. Lin, aren't you?

359
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,444
How did you get up here?

360
00:15:16,643 --> 00:15:18,403
The third floor is no place for you!

361
00:15:20,244 --> 00:15:21,163
Answer me!

362
00:15:21,163 --> 00:15:22,124
Who let you come up?

363
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:23,643
Are you deaf?

364
00:15:23,643 --> 00:15:25,444
- I came with Mr. Bai.
- I arranged it.

365
00:15:26,244 --> 00:15:26,964
Mr. Tu.

366
00:15:29,364 --> 00:15:30,043
Mr. Tu.

367
00:15:30,523 --> 00:15:31,844
My apologies, Mr. Tu.

368
00:15:32,043 --> 00:15:34,364
I didn't know it was your arrangement.

369
00:15:36,163 --> 00:15:36,763
You,

370
00:15:37,364 --> 00:15:38,043
go over there.

371
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,204
You,

372
00:15:39,803 --> 00:15:40,403
come here.

373
00:15:45,844 --> 00:15:46,604
Hello, Mr. Tu.

374
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:05,774
♪If the heart can't hear the sorrow♪

375
00:16:06,073 --> 00:16:09,264
♪It only makes everything look so fake♪

376
00:16:10,976 --> 00:16:14,717
♪Your eyes resemble hers too much♪

377
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:18,065
♪Who makes me forget whom♪

378
00:16:19,536 --> 00:16:23,266
♪The warmth in my heart is fading♪

379
00:16:23,490 --> 00:16:27,072
♪Every glance feels like atonement♪

380
00:16:28,386 --> 00:16:32,160
♪Ambiguity hidden in the night breeze♪

381
00:16:32,711 --> 00:16:37,826
♪Blows away the chance to explain♪

382
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:42,664
♪I feel guilty♪

383
00:16:43,234 --> 00:16:46,978
♪I'll have no regrets
even I leave quietly♪

384
00:16:47,842 --> 00:16:51,285
♪Even in tears♪

385
00:16:52,034 --> 00:16:55,948
♪It doesn't matter♪

386
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:59,953
♪We embrace in dreams♪

387
00:17:00,802 --> 00:17:04,240
♪I let down all my defenses♪

388
00:17:05,474 --> 00:17:08,837
♪Though the story has its end♪

389
00:17:09,602 --> 00:17:17,954
♪I'll journey with you all my life♪
